README: Next.js Notifications Frontend (implementation plan + full file templates)

Purpose
-
This file contains a concrete plan and full-file templates to implement a responsive React/Next.js frontend that consumes the evaluation notifications API.

Goals (as required)
- Build All Notifications page and Priority Notifications page.
- Support limit, page, notification_type query params.
- Distinguish new vs viewed notifications via frontend (localStorage) and allow marking as seen.
- Use Material UI for styling (fallback to native CSS only if MUI unavailable).
- Robust error handling and responsive design (desktop + mobile).

Quick instructions
-
1) Create project

	 npx create-next-app@latest campus-notifications --use-npm --app
	 cd campus-notifications

2) Install dependencies

	 npm install @mui/material @emotion/react @emotion/styled axios

3) Add the following files (copy contents from the templates below).

