Notes and assumptions
-
- The API returns either an array or an object with a 'notifications' array; code checks both.
- Notifications must have a unique 'id' field; if not, use another unique key.
- localStorage key 'viewed_notifications_v1' stores array of ids for seen notifications. This is the frontend-only mechanism to distinguish new vs seen.
- To capture mobile and desktop views for submission, run the dev server (npm run dev) and record screens.

